  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "One of the primary bottlenecks of performing MD with ML potentials lies in the time integration itself.",
    "The equations of motion must be solved with a small time step -typically in the order of 0.5 to 1 femtosecond -to resolve high-frequency motions such as bond vibrations.",
    "With computationally intensive ML models, this results in a high number of expensive force evaluations, further amplifying the overall simulation cost.",
    "Multi-Time-Step (MTS) integrators [22] [23] [24] offer a well-established strategy to address this challenge.",
    "Originally introduced in the context of classical molecular simulations, MTS methods such as RESPA (Reference System Propagator Algorithm) 22 exploit the separation of timescales between different components of the forces to reduce the number of expensive evaluations."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Multi-Time-Step (MTS) integrators [22] [23] [24] offer a well-established strategy to address this challenge.",
